Ensemble Technique Project

Background :- This is a historical data of collected by Bank, which shows thier customer details. On basis of this historical details, we need to build a model which helps their tele marketing team to know about customer behavior and target those customer which have higher chances to take the term deposit subscription. By using this model tele marketing team can utilize thier effort in right direction. This will not only allow the bank to secure deposits more effectively but also increase customer satisfaction by reducing undesirable advertisements for certain customers.

Steps Taken :- 1 :- Import libraries, load data 2 :- Data Intuition (Understand the data structure, Glimps of Data) 3 :- Imputation (missing values and Outliers handling) 4 :- EDA (Exploratory Data Analysis) 5 :- Insight Reports, Visual Graphics 6 :- Transforming categorical veriable in dummies 7 :- Split the dataset in training and test dataset 8 :- Scaling the dataset 9 :- Model building 10:- Model Tuning 11:- Confusion Matrix 12:- OOB Score Calculation 13:- Stacking 14:- Final Score prediction 15:- Selecting high score feature and making model on it 16:- Summary 17:- Conclusion 18:- Suggession

Attributes :-

1 - age (numeric), in Years 2 - job : type of job (categorical: 'admin.','blue-collar','entrepreneur','housemaid','management','retired','self- employed','services','student','technician','unemployed','unknown') 3 - marital : marital status (categorical: 'divorced','married','single'; note: 'divorced' means divorced or widowed)

4 - education: (categorical: 'primary', 'secondary', 'tertiary', 'unknown') 5 - default: has credit in default? (Binary: 'no','yes') 6 - housing: has housing loan? (binary: 'no','yes') 7 - loan: has personal loan? (binary: 'no','yes')

8 - contact: contact communication type (categorical: 'cellular','telephone') 9 - month: last contact month of year (categorical: 'jan', 'feb', 'mar', ..., 'nov', 'dec') 10 - day: last contact day (categorical: 1,2 ,3 ,4 ......, 30, 31) 11 - duration: last contact duration, in seconds (numeric).

12 - campaign: number of contacts performed during this campaign and for this client (numeric, includes last contact) 13 - pdays: number of days that passed by after the client was last contacted from a previous campaign (numeric; 999 means client was not previously contacted) 14 - previous: number of contacts performed before this campaign and for this client (numeric) 15 - poutcome: outcome of the previous marketing campaign (categorical: 'failure','unknown','success') 16 - balance :-Balance present in customer account (numeric)

Output variable (desired target): 17 - Target - has the client subscribed a term deposit? (binary: 'yes','no')

def convert(df4, new_column, old_column):
    df4[new_column] = df4[old_column].apply(lambda x : 0 if x == 'no' else 1)
    return df4[new_column].value_counts()

Insights: target the youngest and the oldest instead of the middle-aged

Green vertical bars indicate that clients with a age of 60+ have the highest subscription rate. About 17% of the subscriptions came from the clients aged between 18 to 29. More than 50% of the subscriptions are contributed by the youngest and the eldest clients.

However, red vertical bars show that the bank focused its marketing efforts on the middle-aged group, which returned lower subscription rates than the younger and older groups. Thus, to make the marketing campaign more effective, the bank should target younger and older clients in the future.

Insight :- Do higher tele marketing campaign in 1st and last quarter.

Earlier campaign timing was wrong.

1 :- The bank contacted most clients between May and August. The highest contact rate is around 30%, which happened in May, while the contact rate is closer to 0 in March, September, October, and December. 2 :- However, the subscription rate showed a different trend. The highest subscription rate occurred in March, which is over 50%, and all subscription rates in September, October, and December are over 40%.

Clearly, these two lines move in different directions which strongly indicates the inappropriate timing of the bank’s marketing campaign. To improve the marketing campaign, the bank should consider initiating the telemarketing campaign in starting and ending of the year, when the subscription rate tends to be higher. however need to collect more data in future to check if this trend is consistent or not.

Since data was biased and subscriber and non subscriber was not in equal strength, Hence we are able to predict good about the customer who will not subscribe rather than who will subscribe for the term deposit. Since Recall of non subscriber is 98% while recall for subscriber is only 36 % in best performing model i.e. Gradient Boosting.

However, the result of accuracy score can possibly yield misleading result if the data set is unbalanced, because the number of observations in different classes largely vary.

A problem revealed by this confusion matrix is that the dataset is highly unbalanced, with nearly all client actually decline to subscribe. This infers that the accuracy score is biased, and further evaluation should be carried out.

using hypothesis testing on 95% confidance level for model to work well in production. As per OOB Score 91% and validation Score 91% for Random forest let's declare null and alternate hypothesis.

Ho = production score PS = 91 % H1 = production Score PS != 91% Alpha = 0.05%

# let's create a function which will compare P-value with Alpha = 0.05 and tell us if P-value is > than or < than the Alpha

def p_val_status(p_val):
    if p_val >= 0.05:
        print('Since P value is greater than Alpha hence Do not reject the Null Hypothesis (Ho)')
    else:
        print('Since P value is less than Alpha hence Accept the Alternate Hypothesis (H1)')

                            Summary :-

1:- Data is biased because the number of observations in different classes largely vary. 2:- Data is not normally distributed. 3:- Variables doesn't have strong correlation. 4:- Lot of outliers were present. Also some missing values was there in form of 'Unknown' and 'other'. 5:- Lot of object variable (string values) were present in dataset. 6:- Youngest and Oldest age group took more subscription than middle age groups. 7:- Higher Balance customer took more subscription than lower or no balance customer. 8:- Student, Singles took more subscription than any other category. 9:- In Feb, March, Apr and Sept, Oct, Nov months subscription rate was highest. 10:-Campaign Timing was wrong and campaign was done higher in non prouctive months. 11:-Tele Marketing team have targeted wrong customer during campaign. 12:-Majority of customers called is in the age of 30s and 40s (33 to 48 years old fall within the 25th to 75th percentiles). The distribution of customer age is fairly normal with a small standard deviation. 13:-The distribution of balance has a huge standard deviation relative to the mean, suggesting large variabilities in customers' balance levels. 14:-There is no clear relationship between client’s age and balance level. Nevertheless, over the age of 60, clients tend to have a significantly lower balance, mostly under 5,000 euros. 15:-About half of the clients have been contacted by the bank for the second time, while 25% was first introduced to the term deposit. Most clients have been reached by the bank for one to three times, which is reasonable. However, some clients have been contacted by as high as 58 times, which is not normal. These clients may have some special needs that require frequent contact. 16:-Naive Bayse, Decision Tree model didn't perform well, however Random Forest and Gradient Boosting model out performed others. 17:-Stacking was not worked well and out performed by Random Forest and Gradient Boosting. 18:-Recall for non subscriber is very high while recall for subscriber is very low. 19:-OOB score was 91% while Validation Score was 92% for Random Forest. 20:-Most important Feature based Random Forest model was not able to out perform Random Forest and Gradient Boosting models. 21:- Gradient Boosting out performed Random Forest model slightly.

                                Conclusion:-

1:- According to previous analysis, a target customer profile can be established. The most responsive customers possess these features:

Feature 1: age < 30 or age > 60 Feature 2: students or retired people Feature 3: a balance of more than 5000 euros

2:- predicting duration before calling and adjusting marketing plan benefit both the bank and its clients. On the one hand, it will increase the efficiency of the bank’s telemarketing campaign, saving time and efforts. On the other hand, it prevents some clients from receiving undesirable advertisements, raising customer satisfaction.

3:- With the aid of Gradient Boosting or Random Forest, the bank can enter a virtuous cycle of effective marketing, more investments and happier customers.

4:- Dataset was biased so need to collect more samples for positive customer to increase the accuracy of subscriber.

Recommendations

1:- More appropriate timing :- When implementing a marketing strategy, external factors, such as the time of calling, should also be carefully considered. The previous analysis points out that March, September, October and December had the highest success rates. Nevertheless, more data should be collected and analyzed to make sure that this seasonal effect is constant over time.If the trend has the potential to continue in the future, the bank should consider initiating its telemarketing campaign in March, September, October and December.

2:- Choosing right customer :- Since youngest and oldest were the top customer, campaing should be more focused on targeting this age group customers.
